il3WUH1IanJoyOol1wPXND3AQ47BlayaR3_8KTMxf-6VQpkAOlkDFt2jyeA1MwrfDveyWttC4b\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Java compilation**\\n\\nI’m looking into whether CompileTestJava has created duplicate classes because it generated classes on the classpath while compiling Java source with the same fully qualified name (FQN). I see that there's a source file for closure46 with the same class name, but the build.gradle also generated a class with that name. It seems like the compileTestJava compiles the source file while including the generated .class, which might allow duplicates. I need to think about the classpath order here too!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Streamlining code structure**\\n\\nI notice we have a direct helper along with some unused methods like `resolve`. It might make sense to remove `resolveWithCompilerGeneratedClassResolver` and `classResolver` since they seem to be unnecessary now. However, it looks like `MethodHandle` is needed for the constructor and `doCall`, so I’ll keep that. I should also clean up the imports and tests that are no longer relevant, as they contribute to unnecessary noise. The new direct helper and previous tests should cover everything effectively. Time to make these edits carefully!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_VN7ol5TSjIseI8j4To7SpKMS|fc_08edacfb1674bd94016a00eedef16081978935d8ae92ab5b70", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/RequestSpecificationImplInner_getUnnamedPathParamValues_closure43Test.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.List;", "newText": "import java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.util.List;"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void javaReflectionDispatchInvokesCompilerGeneratedClassResolver() throws Throwable {\n        try {\n            Method classResolver = closureClass().getDeclaredMethod(\"class$\", String.class);\n            classResolver.setAccessible(true);\n\n            Object resolvedClass = classResolver.invoke(null, RequestSpecificationImpl.class.getName());\n\n            assertSame(RequestSpecificationImpl.class, resolvedClass);\n        } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\n            rethrowUnlessNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(exception.getCause());\n        } catch (LinkageError error) {\n            assertNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(error);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedNativeImageError(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void javaReflectionDispatchReportsMissingClassFromCompilerGeneratedResolver() throws Throwable {\n        try {\n            Method classResolver = closureClass().getDeclaredMethod(\"class$\", String.class);\n            classResolver.setAccessible(true);\n\n            classResolver.invoke(null, MISSING_CLASS_NAME);\n            throw new AssertionError(\"Missing classes should be reported as NoClassDefFoundError\");\n        } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\n            Throwable cause = exception.getCause();\n            if (cause instanceof NoClassDefFoundError error) {\n                if (isNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(error)) {\n                    return;\n                }\n                assertEquals(MISSING_CLASS_NAME, error.getMessage());\n                return;\n            }\n            rethrowUnlessNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(cause);\n        } catch (LinkageError error) {\n            assertNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(error);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedNativeImageError(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n", "newText": ""}, {"oldText": "    private static Class<?> resolveWithCompilerGeneratedClassResolver(String className) throws Throwable {\n        return (Class<?>) classResolver().invokeExact(className);\n  